result.name: Assaggio Trattoria Italiana

reviews.text: It’s nice place and good food
The risotto was super hard and I had to ask them to reheat twice to make it softer. Oh, and thanks chef for leaving crab shell in my risotto with crab meat which almost broke my teeth!!!
Fantastic place.  Quiet, art ambient, nice restaurant.  Prefect Victoria harbour view.  Very good Italian authentic food.  Near HK Convention and Exhibition Center.

reviews.author_name: 旅。攝手記- NOTE on LIFE with ME
reviews.text: It’s the 2nd time I have been here and it still looks amazing! This time we are lucky enough to have a window seat view. The ambiance is great with a brilliant Victoria harbour view. It’s ideal for couples or friends gathering. In terms of food, we ordered cold cuts, pizza and meatballs. I love the cold cuts and meatball the most! Everything looks yum and definitely will be back.
Very good quality food for its price. Just location is very inconvenient.  A long walk from mtr, and located inside arts center,  so harder to find

Horrible service, avoid this place at all cost, definitely won't come again.
